##Code and query to print all the data after joining Teams and Salaries tables
salary_query = '''SELECT Teams.yearID AS Year, Teams.teamID AS Team, Teams.name AS Name, Teams.W AS Win, Teams.G AS Game, 
                ((CAST(Teams.W AS FLOAT)/CAST(Teams.G AS FLOAT))*100) AS Win_Per 
                FROM Teams 
                INNER JOIN Salaries ON Teams.yearID = Salaries.yearID AND Teams.teamID = Salaries.teamID 
                GROUP BY Teams.teamID, Teams.yearID'''

result = pd.read_sql(salary_query, conn)
(result)

#For the desired output using SQL query and python; I used an inner join which is also known as join in sql to join tables Teams and Salaries.
#I join based on the columns yearID and teamID as these two columns where common columns present in both tables followed by grouping accordingly.
#Further with joining, I do the computation to compute the winning percentage which was ((win/games)*100) as Win_Per column in my result table or 
#dataframe.
#I cast the columns win and game to float to get the desired percentage in our floating point values.
#Therefore, my desired output table or dataframe has 6 columns with year, team, name of the teams as name, win, game and winning percentage as win_per.

##Code and query to print all the data after joining Teams and Salaries tables
salary_query = '''SELECT Teams.yearID AS Year, Teams.teamID AS TeamID, Teams.name AS Name, Teams.W AS Win, Teams.G AS Game, 
                    Teams.franchID AS FranchiseID, ((CAST(Teams.W AS FLOAT)/CAST(Teams.G AS FLOAT))*100) AS Win_Per 
                    FROM Teams 
                    INNER JOIN Salaries ON Teams.yearID = Salaries.yearID AND Teams.teamID = Salaries.teamID 
                    GROUP BY Teams.teamID, Teams.yearID'''

result = pd.read_sql(salary_query, conn)

Part 3: Data transformations¶

Standardizing across years¶

Problem 5¶

In [250]:
prob5 = prob4.copy()
In [251]:
result = prob5.groupby('Year')['total_payroll'].mean()
pay_avg = result.to_frame()
pay_avg.reset_index(inplace=True)
pay_avg.columns = ['Year', 'avg']

result = prob5.groupby('Year')['total_payroll'].std()
pay_std = result.to_frame()
pay_std.reset_index(inplace=True)
pay_std.columns = ['Year', 'std']
In [252]:
prob5["avg"] = 0.0
prob5["std"] = 0.0
In [253]:
for index1, row1 in prob5.iterrows():
    for index2, row2 in pay_avg.iterrows():
        if(row1['Year'] == row2['Year']):
            row1['avg'] = row2['avg']
            
            prob5._set_value(index1,'avg',row2['avg'])
        else:
            pass

for index1, row1 in prob5.iterrows():
    for index2, row2 in pay_std.iterrows():
        if(row1['Year'] == row2['Year']):
            row1['std'] = row2['std']
            prob5._set_value(index1,'std',row2['std'])
        else:
            pass
In [254]:
prob5['standardized_payroll'] = (prob5['total_payroll'] - prob5['avg'])/prob5['std']
